  <front>
    <title>Reporting MUD behavior to vendors</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-lear-opsawg-mud-reporter-00"/>
    <author initials="E." surname="Lear" fullname="Eliot Lear">
      <organization>Cisco Systems</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="M." surname="Ranganathan" fullname="Mudumbai Ranganathan">
      <organization>NIST</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="05" month="July" year="2019"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   As with other technology, manufacturers would like to understand how
   networks implementing MUD are treating devices that are providing MUD
   URLs and MUD files.  This memo specifies an extension to MUD that
   permits certain behaviors to be reported.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
